ion above them, and even to the social lives of herders at remote livestock posts. As we enter our planet's water-export era, Lesotho exposes the possibilities and perils ahead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aWater resources developmentxEnvironmental aspectszLesotho. 0aWater transferzLesotho. 0aWater-supplyzLesotho. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052038635840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520386358423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520386358/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY